@node INTRODUCTION "Introduction"

 If you ever missed the powerful features of the REBOL language in your favourite
 programming language (in my case E) then this one is for you.

 It's a shared library that can be accessed from nearly any programming language.
 It allows executing REBOL code from within your preferred language.
 Actually it is calling the REBOL interpreter in the background. But you don't
 have to care about it.

@endnode

