@node FEATURES "Features"

 Quite easy to use ! What else do I have to say..

@endnode

@node REQUIREMENTS "Requirements"

 · AmigaOS/68K >= Release 3.0 (Version 39). Maybe older releases do work as well ?

   Should run under AROS/68K and MorphOS/PPC as well. Couldn't test this.

 · 68000 (compatible) or higher

 · ca.5 MB of free memory

@endnode

@node INSTALLATION "Installation"

 Automatically:

  No Installer script, sorry.


 Manually:

  Copy Libs/rebol.library to LIBS:

  Copy Help/English/RebolLib.guide to Help:English/


 Developers only:

  Put the appropriate include files to your Includes directory and Autodocs/rebol.doc
  to your Autodocs directory.

  IMPORTANT NOTE:

  The Include files for Assembler,BASIC,C have been created using Dirk Stöcker's
  FD2Pragma. As I don't use these languages myself they are not tested. If there
  is a problem, please report me !
  A demo is currently only available for E. If you'd like to convert it to other
  languages, I would be pleasured. Include files for other languages and additional
  demos are welcome , too.

@endnode

@node USAGE "Usage"

 Users:

 There's nothing you have to do.

 Developers:

 Have a look at the Autodoc file.


@endnode

@node CONFIGURATION "Configuration"

 Check if you have a proper Rebol installation:
 The @{b}REBOL_HOME@{ub} environment variable must be set correctly to your Rebol directory.
 The directory name must end in : or / character !
 The Rebol interpreter executable must be called @{b}Rebol@{ub}. Be careful if
 you use a filesystem that works with case sensitive file names !

@endnode

@endnode

@node BUGS "Bugs"

 No bugs known so far. If you get some problems, please get in contact with @{"me" link CONTACT}.

 Not really a bug, but a big problem is the speed. This has two reasons:

 · There is no PPC version of the rebol interpreter

 · making the interpreter resident to speed up starting doesn't work with newer
   REBOL versions

@endnode

